<DocsLayout title="Installation">
  <h1>Installation</h1>

  <p class="lead text-xl text-neutral-600">
    Deploy Vendel on your own server for production use.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 alert alert-info">
    <p>
      <strong>Don't want to self-host?</strong> Try <a href="https://app.vendel.cc" class="text-accent hover:underline">Vendel Cloud</a> — free plan available, paid plans from $0.99/month.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Requirements</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Linux server (Ubuntu 22.04+ recommended)</li>
    <li>At least 512MB RAM, 5GB disk</li>
    <li>Domain name with SSL certificate</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Option 1: Docker Compose (Recommended)</h2>

  <p>Requires <a href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/">Docker</a> and Docker Compose v2.</p>

  <h3>1. Create docker-compose.yml</h3>

  <p>Create a new directory and add a <code>docker-compose.yml</code> file:</p>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="yaml"
    filename="docker-compose.yml"
    code={`services:
  app:
    image: ghcr.io/jimscope/vendel:latest
    environment:
      - ENVIRONMENT=production
      - FIRST_SUPERUSER=\${FIRST_SUPERUSER}
      - FIRST_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD=\${FIRST_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD}
      - APP_URL=https://\${DOMAIN}
      - FRONTEND_URL=https://\${DOMAIN}
      - WEBHOOK_ENCRYPTION_KEY=\${WEBHOOK_ENCRYPTION_KEY:-}
      - FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=\${FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON:-}
      - SMTP_HOST=\${SMTP_HOST:-}
      - SMTP_PORT=\${SMTP_PORT:-}
      - SMTP_USERNAME=\${SMTP_USERNAME:-}
      - SMTP_PASSWORD=\${SMTP_PASSWORD:-}
    ports:
      - "8090:8090"
    volumes:
      - vendel_data:/app/pb_data

volumes:
  vendel_data:`}
  />

  <h3>2. Configure environment</h3>

  <p>Create a <code>.env</code> file in the same directory:</p>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="bash"
    filename=".env"
    code={`# Required
FIRST_SUPERUSER=admin@yourdomain.com
FIRST_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD=your-secure-password
DOMAIN=sms.yourdomain.com
WEBHOOK_ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-random-32-character-string

# Firebase (required for push notifications to Android devices)
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account",...}

# SMTP (optional, for email features)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.yourdomain.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USERNAME=noreply@yourdomain.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-smtp-password`}
  />

  <h3>3. Start the service</h3>

  <CodeBlock lang="bash" code="docker compose up -d" />

  <h3>4. Access the dashboard</h3>

  <p>Open the dashboard at <code>https://sms.yourdomain.com</code> (or <code>http://localhost:8090</code> if testing locally). Log in with the superuser credentials from your <code>.env</code> file. The PocketBase admin panel is available at <code>/_/</code>.</p>

  <h3>5. Update to a new version</h3>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="bash"
    code={`docker compose pull
docker compose up -d`}
  />

  <h2>Option 2: Standalone Binary</h2>

  <p>No Docker needed. Download a single archive that contains the server binary and the pre-built frontend.</p>

  <h3>1. Download</h3>

  <p>Go to <a href="https://github.com/JimScope/vendel/releases">GitHub Releases</a> and download the archive for your platform:</p>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
    <a href="https://github.com/JimScope/vendel/releases/latest/download/vendel_linux_amd64.tar.gz" class="card card-default no-underline hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]" style="transition: border-color 0.2s">
      <h4 class="card-title">Linux x86_64</h4>
      <p class="card-description">amd64 &middot; .tar.gz</p>
    </a>
    <a href="https://github.com/JimScope/vendel/releases/latest/download/vendel_linux_arm64.tar.gz" class="card card-default no-underline hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]" style="transition: border-color 0.2s">
      <h4 class="card-title">Linux ARM64</h4>
      <p class="card-description">Raspberry Pi 4+, Oracle Cloud &middot; .tar.gz</p>
    </a>
    <a href="https://github.com/JimScope/vendel/releases/latest/download/vendel_linux_arm.tar.gz" class="card card-default no-underline hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]" style="transition: border-color 0.2s">
      <h4 class="card-title">Linux ARM</h4>
      <p class="card-description">armv7 &middot; .tar.gz</p>
    </a>
    <a href="https://github.com/JimScope/vendel/releases/latest/download/vendel_darwin_amd64.tar.gz" class="card card-default no-underline hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]" style="transition: border-color 0.2s">
      <h4 class="card-title">macOS Intel</h4>
      <p class="card-description">amd64 &middot; .tar.gz</p>
    </a>
    <a href="https://github.com/JimScope/vendel/releases/latest/download/vendel_darwin_arm64.tar.gz" class="card card-default no-underline hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]" style="transition: border-color 0.2s">
      <h4 class="card-title">macOS Apple Silicon</h4>
      <p class="card-description">arm64 &middot; .tar.gz</p>
    </a>
    <a href="https://github.com/JimScope/vendel/releases/latest/download/vendel_windows_amd64.zip" class="card card-default no-underline hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]" style="transition: border-color 0.2s">
      <h4 class="card-title">Windows x86_64</h4>
      <p class="card-description">amd64 &middot; .zip</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h3>2. Extract</h3>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="bash"
    code={`tar xzf vendel_linux_amd64.tar.gz
ls
# vendel        <- server binary
# pb_public/    <- pre-built frontend`}
  />

  <h3>3. Configure environment</h3>

  <p>Create a <code>.env</code> file in the same directory as the binary:</p>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="bash"
    filename=".env"
    code={`ENVIRONMENT=production
FIRST_SUPERUSER=admin@yourdomain.com
FIRST_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD=your-secure-password
WEBHOOK_ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-random-32-character-string
APP_URL=https://yourdomain.com
FRONTEND_URL=https://yourdomain.com`}
  />

  <p>Or export them directly:</p>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="bash"
    code={`export WEBHOOK_ENCRYPTION_KEY="your-random-32-character-string"
export FIRST_SUPERUSER="admin@yourdomain.com"
export FIRST_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD="your-secure-password"
export APP_URL="https://yourdomain.com"
export FRONTEND_URL="https://yourdomain.com"`}
  />

  <h3>4. Start the server</h3>

  <CodeBlock lang="bash" code="./vendel serve --http=0.0.0.0:8090" />

  <p>PocketBase creates a <code>pb_data/</code> directory for the SQLite database on first run. The dashboard is available at <code>http://localhost:8090</code>.</p>

  <h3>5. Run as a systemd service</h3>

  <p>For production, run Vendel as a systemd service so it starts on boot and restarts on failure:</p>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="ini"
    filename="/etc/systemd/system/vendel.service"
    code={`[Unit]
Description=Vendel SMS Gateway
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=vendel
WorkingDirectory=/opt/vendel
ExecStart=/opt/vendel/vendel serve --http=0.0.0.0:8090
EnvironmentFile=/opt/vendel/.env
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=5

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target`}
  />

  <CodeBlock lang="bash" code="sudo systemctl enable --now vendel" />

  <h3>6. Update to a new version</h3>

  <p>Download the new release, replace the binary and <code>pb_public/</code> folder, then restart:</p>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="bash"
    code={`tar xzf vendel_linux_amd64.tar.gz
sudo systemctl restart vendel`}
  />

  <h2>Reverse Proxy Setup</h2>

  <p>Vendel runs on port <code>8090</code>. Place a reverse proxy in front for HTTPS. See <a href="/docs/guides/nginx">Nginx Reverse Proxy</a> for a full guide, or use Caddy for automatic SSL:</p>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="text"
    filename="Caddyfile"
    code={`yourdomain.com {
    reverse_proxy localhost:8090
}`}
  />

  <h2>Environment Variables</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Variable</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Default</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>ENVIRONMENT</code></td>
        <td>Runtime environment (<code>local</code> or <code>production</code>)</td>
        <td>local</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>FIRST_SUPERUSER</code></td>
        <td>Superuser email address</td>
        <td>admin@vendel.cc</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>FIRST_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD</code></td>
        <td>Superuser password</td>
        <td>changethis</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>WEBHOOK_ENCRYPTION_KEY</code></td>
        <td>AES key for webhook secret encryption (random 32+ char string)</td>
        <td>-</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>APP_URL</code></td>
        <td>Public URL of the application</td>
        <td>http://localhost:8090</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>FRONTEND_URL</code></td>
        <td>Public URL for frontend redirects</td>
        <td>http://localhost:5173</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON</code></td>
        <td>Firebase service account JSON for FCM push notifications</td>
        <td>-</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>SMTP_HOST</code> / <code>SMTP_PORT</code></td>
        <td>SMTP server for sending emails</td>
        <td>localhost:1025</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>SMTP_USERNAME</code> / <code>SMTP_PASSWORD</code></td>
        <td>SMTP credentials</td>
        <td>-</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Backup with Litestream</h2>

  <p>Vendel uses SQLite as its embedded database. For continuous backup to S3-compatible storage, set these optional environment variables:</p>

  <CodeBlock
    lang="bash"
    code={`LITESTREAM_REPLICA_URL=s3://my-bucket/vendel/data
LITESTREAM_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key
LITESTREAM_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-key`}
  />

  <p>When set, Litestream automatically streams WAL changes to your S3 bucket and restores on startup if needed.</p>

